rComments: A lot of emphasis on the textbook. Lectures are interesting but tests are very inconsistent. Never know what to expect: sometimes they are easy and sometimes impossible. Assignment is easy to get a good grade on. Focuses a lot on his own research and his own academic accomplishments.

Took thesis class and IRP with him. Even though there was a lot of responsibility, you will feel very much rewarded for your hardwork. My experience with Dr. Schellenberg was nothing but motivational. You do your part and you will accomplish your goals.
Brilliant ideas and research methodology, makes you understand complicated research in an easy straightforward method.

Awesome prof! Seems hard to approach but is actually really nice and helpful. He wants his students to succeed but he's going to make you work for it. Very high but very clear expectations! Go to class, do your readings, study and you will do well.

All about the studies he teaches you in class. MC based on book..as long as you read you're basically ensured a 50% on every midterm. Easy Essay. Short Answers always ALWAYS on studies he taught-very specific/hard/irrelevant..hated the 3 hour class.

Originally, I wasn't incredibly enthusiastic about Devpsych. For me, Schellenburg's class ignited a new interest in the topic. However, the class is not a walk in the park. Pay. Attention. To. The. STUDIES! He will not simply feed good marks to you: like any good teacher, he will make you work for them, and will eventually make them work for you.
He's pretty interesting. The textbook is very important in this course, especially if you wanna do well on m/c. His short answer questions are based on case studies. Quite a bit of memorization

A good prof with some interesting lectures...he kind of ran out of steam at the end of the year, though. It is difficult to do well in his class. If you are in DevPsych, take lots of time to understand the material. That means read the textbook, go to class and STUDY!

I didn't like him at first, but I like him a lot now.  His tests are hard, but easy if you study--TRUST ME. Study.  Especially those experiments/studies.  Your textbook is your bff.  Take good notes in class.  The stuff he writes on the board= important.  Sit near the front.  Print your notes beforehand.  Read before going to class!

Ditto to everyone mentioning hard course. A lot of work and precise note taking on the case-studies is a must. Overall he can teach and hes a little weird...Also he sweats a lot lol. Back of his shirt will make you think he just did some interval sprints.
impossible work load, makes you wanna give up, the extra studies are pointless as there are alot on the book already
I like him, i do think that its difficult to do really well though.  big work load
crazy work load, read the text, read the assigned reading, study and remember the methods and results for the studies he covered in class. Takes time to study! good luck, seriously
Great prof! Based on current research studies being done in the field - very interesting and fun!!

Prof was very rude and unapproachable, sometimes could be very strange...class was qute difficult and a lot of attention was paid to useless details...will never take any classes offered by him again.

His writing is HORRIFIC!! I stood up close and still could not make sense of the word. He is not someone I would approach for help... Case studies = whole course. He focuses on the little detail of the case studies rather than the concept of it, which I find very useless as these will not help in the future. His notes are garbage.

Not too bad of a prof (or course) when it comes to teaching style,helpfulness etc. The only negative was having to memorize a million different studies. He's also a bit too picky on the multiple choice questions. Lectures were interesting enough.
He is great!  He makes sure we all understand a concept!  he's commited to his students!
Worst handwriting ever, class boring, dunno why he's still teaching.

Agree with rest of the posters that he appears rather intimidating, and that he is not very approachable. Having said that, I appreciate his lectures very much...he challenges you to think. Exams were a mix of easy/straight out of notes to more abstract questions requiring understanding of underlying concepts vs. details.
Great prof!

The only good think is the text that he selected. Rest of the course is just waste of our money and time. It is all about memorizing details of many many American profs' studies . Schellenberg likes to make comments that will most likekely offend at least few people in his huge class. He shouldn't try to be funny.

Heavy load of material... Expected to memorize the textbook and tedious details (i.e. design/method) from the research given (usually about 5 examples per class).  However, the research gives you meaning behind the information in the textbook and are interesting to learn.  Uses many methods of teaching which keeps you awake during the 3hr lecture.

I had a bad impression of him to start with. but i think he is an excellent prof! he is able keep me focused in a 3-hr lecture! by using all methods of teaching like using slides, writing on the board, overheads. he might not be the nicest prof, but he's sure good at lecturing.

Hmm, He's an OK proff. Not very nice..not very mean.Hard to get an A in his class. His tests for this class were out of a mere 30 marks, so therefore if u screw up a bit, there goes ur mark. MCQ were annoying b/c I hated the textbook!

This prof loves to fudge with your marks so that he doesn't get in trouble for having a high class average. For example, the TA marked our tests and they were too high according to him so he regraded them.
Tough, good lecturer, despite the fact that he hates lecturing and cares only abotu his research. :P  But knows his stuff - a tough class, but you'll learn a lot.

Have only taken PSY210 with him...HATE how he focuses on others' research (studies). Think it's pointless to memorize little details about studies for a test....and he gives TONS of examples from different studies.
Kinda of mean, nasal voice,I don't like him

Great prof overall...but a little apathetic to children (especially the ones with William's Syndrome...) He needs to be careful with what he says because he really offended some people (especially people who know or have kids with developmental disabilities) with some of the things he said.

Very good lecturer - made class interesting.Tests aren't at all hard in terms of applying/understanding the material - they just require A LOT of memory work.Know everything (text & lectures) - even the stuff that doesn't seem important, and KNOW THE STUDIES (you'll pick up a lot of marks there).
CRAZY PROF!! This guy scares me with his eye brows and mean expression.  His course are boring, difficult and plus he's quite rude and arrogant. don't take it unless u have to
No Comments
Very Funny

Awesome professor. Know the studies he presents in class for sure. He's really nice if you go to him for help. Makes class interesting too. First test is usually harder, mark goes up for sure after that.
Really good prof - lectures well - easy to understand - tests aren't too hard - don't try to get any help if you're a girl - not very nice - a lot nicer to boys
Excellent Prof! He's very engaging and made the subject very interesting by using excellent examples.
He makes the 1st test hard and the 2nd test easy so that u don't screw up AFTER the drop date. Exam was easy but essay was marked hard.
Eh...pay close attention to details.
Not bad, nice guy. Just attend lectures and make sure to know all studies he covers.  for tests make sure to focus on lectures.

I think he's a good prof.  Make sure to pay close attention to all the studies he does.  If u don't understand...ask...coz it'll surely come on the test.  The course is really interesting and if u do ur work, u can get an A in his class...I did!
Tough professor, but excellent lecturer. The class was great! Challenges his students. Take one of his classes!
Developmental psychology was hard
I really liked him...thought he was brilliant. Pay attention, do your work, and you will learn alot.
WORST PROF EVER!
Don't get me started on the 1,001 studies! LOL. Difficult course but I liked it ALOT. If you hate memorization don't take it because you'll need to memorize studies & results inside & out.
very difficult course...too many studies to remember...
very rude; really difficult course; turned me off psych; had to change my major
Unbelievably Hard-assed prof. that I think I've learned every study in the world
No Comments
